-- Macquarie Hires Kazi for Fixed Income, Currencies (Correct)
-- Claire Leow
-- 2010-07-20T02:00:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-19/macquarie-hires-kazi-as-head-of-currencies-commodities-business-in-asia.html

          
          
             (Corrects headline in story first published July 19.)  
 Macquarie Group Ltd., Australia’s
largest investment bank, hired Mack Kazi for its fixed-income,
currencies and commodities business in Asia.  
 Kazi joined as executive director and head of Asian markets,
based in Singapore, Paul Scanlon, Macquarie’s head of media and
communications in Asia, wrote in an e-mail today in response to
questions from Bloomberg. Scanlon, in a separate phone call,
didn’t say when Kazi had joined the company.  
 Kazi had been regional head of emerging markets trading in
Asia at the Royal Bank of Scotland Group Plc.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
